description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, enthusiastic, self motivated Registered Learning Disability/Registered Mental Health Nurse to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post may be appropriate for newly qualified nurses to gain experience in a hospital setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working with people with learning disabilities and associated and complex health presentations or challenging behaviour would be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be based on Hillside Assessment and Treatment Unit at Ashgreen and work alongside the multi-disciplinary team, partner agencies and carers to support the patients journey and make a difference in ensuring that quality services are delivered with care, compassion and competence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent communication skills and have the ability to plan and organise competent, evidence based clinical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be provided with regular clinical support and supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a clinical employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS way outlined on our website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JOIN OUR OUTSTANDING DCHS FAMILY!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Derbyshire Community Health Services has been rated as an ‘outstanding’ trust by the Care Quality Commission; we have achieved this by providing high quality patient care within an inclusive organisation that works together and shows care and compassion for each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There has never been a more exciting time to join us as one of the largest specialist community NHS providers in the country – one that is also among the very best NHS employers as voted by its own staff and by CQC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The way the NHS works is changing; care outside of traditional hospital settings is quickly becoming a much larger part of what the NHS does. As a leading community provider we are at the forefront of this exciting future, joining-up services in local communities to better meet the individual needs of our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DCHS is a top performing NHS Trust that strives for innovation and improvement for the service and individuals that work within it, we currently have the following opportunity available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way outlined on our website and in the additional information provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Susan Hedley - Nurse Manager&lt;/p&gt;
